#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:47
msgid ""
"Using :kbd:`lmb` in the 3D area will place the 3D cursor directly under your"
" mouse pointer. For accuracy you should use two perpendicular orthogonal 3D "
"views, i.e. any combination of top (:kbd:`pad7`), front (:kbd:`pad1`) and "
"side (:kbd:`pad3`). That way you can control the positioning along two axes "
"in one view and determine depth in the second view."
msgstr ""

