#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:58
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Snap` menu (:kbd:`Shift-S` or :menuselection:`Object/Mesh -->"
" Snap`) will allow you to snap the cursor in the following ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:62
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cursor to Selected`: snaps the cursor to the currently selected "
"vertex, edge or face. In :guilabel:`Object` mode this option will snap the "
"cursor to the center of the currently selected Object."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:63
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cursor to Center`: snaps the cursor to the origin point of the "
"grid (location 0,0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:64
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cursor to Grid`: snaps the cursor to the nearest **visible** part"
" of the grid."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:65
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Cursor to Active`: snaps the cursor to the *active* (last "
"selected) object, edge, face or vertex."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:67
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Cursor to Selected` option is also affected by the number of "
"elements in the selection and the current pivot point.  For example, with "
"several elements selected and the :guilabel:`Bounding Box Center` pivot "
"point active, the :guilabel:`Cursor to Selected` option will snap the 3D "
"cursor to the:"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:73
msgid ""
"**Center of the bounding box** surrounding the objects' centers in "
":guilabel:`Object` mode or the **center of the bounding box** surrounding "
"the selected vertices when in :guilabel:`Edit` mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:75
msgid ""
"When the :guilabel:`Median Point` pivot point is selected, :guilabel:`Cursor"
" to Selected` will snap the 3D cursor to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../manual/3d_interaction/transform_control/pivot_point/3d_cursor.rst:78
msgid ""
"The median of the object centers in :guilabel:`Object` mode and the median "
"of the selected vertices in :guilabel:`Edit` mode."
msgstr ""

